![](Images/yкринформ/2023-04-03T-66-49-10-03-00/630_360_1680543930-584.jpg)The Vokoordination Headquarters on the Defense of prisoners of war took place with the families of servicemen of the 72nd separate mechanized brigade, in particular, it was about social payments to families whose relatives are considered missing.

About it in [](https://t.me/Koord_shtab/778)She reported the press service headquarters on the management of prisoners of war, reports Ukrinform.

“A meeting with the families of servicemen of the 72nd mechanized brigade took place at the Coordination Headquarters. The questions were answered by representatives of the Coordination Staff, the Armed Forces of Ukraine, the National Police and the Advisor for Persons missing in special circumstances Ivanangelin, ”the message reads.

** Read also: ** [](https://www.ukrinform.ua/rubric-ato/3690737-obmin-polonenih-u-koordstabi-rozpovili-pro-robotu-z-miznarodnimi-organizaciami.html)

![](Images/yкринформ/2023-04-03T-66-49-10-03-00/1680544073-583.jpg)It is noted that during the meeting they discussed the investigation after the disappearance of defenders or captives.

“The military unit has 30 days for investigation. The results of the investigation are generally faster. After that, the military part announces the territorial center of acquisition and social support, and he must notify his relatives during the day. Commanders are not obliged to report the questions of relatives. Communication is provided through territorial centers, ”the coordination noted.

** Read also: ** [](https://www.ukrinform.ua/rubric-ato/3690212-ukrainciv-zasteregli-vid-vikoristanna-rosijskih-catbotiv-dla-posuku-polonenih.html)The meeting was also about social payments. The adviser to the missing person, missing in special circumstances, Ivan Angelin noted that when the defender is considered missing and his family formula for minors in connection with the loss of the breadwinner, and then the breadwinner turned from captivity, the money was received.

The staff representative recalled that about a third of the people who were considered missing were returned during exchanges.

As reported, Ukraine has returned 12 more citizens from Russian captivity, including five seriously wounded.

